law.text:
The Kentucky Capitol Centennial Commission shall:
Study and recommend activities that may be conducted throughout the Commonwealth to celebrate the one hundredth anniversary of Kentucky's Capitol;
Educate Kentucky's citizens and the nation about Kentucky's Capitol;
Assist area development districts, local governments, school systems, businesses, organizations, and individuals with planning and preparation of events and projects to educate Kentuckians in all regions of the state about the significance of Kentucky's Capitol;
Serve as the coordinating point for information about the various state, regional, and local activities occurring in Kentucky to celebrate the Capitol's centennial anniversary;
Plan and implement the Capitol's centennial anniversary celebration;
Recommend temporary or permanent improvements to the Capitol grounds to make them more amenable to activities associated with the centennial anniversary;
Perform other duties necessary to highlight the role of Kentucky's Capitol in the Commonwealth's history and for decades to come; and
Seek grants and philanthropic support for activities celebrating the centennial anniversary of Kentucky's Capitol.
